    <briefdescription>
<para>This file defines the key ID ranges of the existing users of the PSA Crypto API. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>In addition to the application, different subsystems store and use persistent keys through the PSA Crypto API. Because they are not aware of each other, collisions are avoided by having them use different ID ranges. This file acts as the registry of all the allocated PSA key ID ranges within Zephyr.</para>
<para>The end-user application also has a dedicated range, <computeroutput>ZEPHYR_PSA_APPLICATION_KEY_ID_RANGE_BEGIN</computeroutput>.</para>
<para>Some of the IDs below are based on previously existing and used values, while others are chosen to be somewhere in the PSA user key ID range to try to avoid collisions (avoiding, for example, the very beginning of the range). </para>
    </detaileddescription>
